# INVENTORY & ASSET MODULE: API STRUCTURE OVERVIEW
1. Product Management (/api/inventory/products)
Method	Route	Description
GET	/products	List all products (with optional filters)
POST	/products	Add new product
GET	/products/:id	View single product
PUT	/products/:id	Update product
DELETE	/products/:id	Delete product

    Filters: ?category=...&brand=...&location=...&keyword=...

2. Stock Movements (/api/inventory/stock-movements)
Method	Route	Description
GET	/stock-movements	List all stock logs (filterable)
POST	/stock-movements	Add stock movement
GET	/stock-movements/:id	View single stock movement

    Filters: ?product_id=...&movement_type=...&date=...

3. Asset Master (/api/inventory/assets)
Method	Route	Description
GET	/assets	List all assets with filters
POST	/assets	Create new asset
GET	/assets/:id	View asset by ID
PUT	/assets/:id	Update asset
DELETE	/assets/:id	Delete asset

    Filters: ?status=...&assigned_to=...&asset_type=...&brand=...

4. Asset Request (/api/inventory/asset-requests)
Method	Route	Description
GET	/asset-requests	List all asset requests
POST	/asset-requests	Submit asset request
GET	/asset-requests/:id	View request
PUT	/asset-requests/:id	Update request
DELETE	/asset-requests/:id	Delete request
5. Master Data
Route	Purpose
/api/inventory/master/categories	
/api/inventory/master/statuses	
/api/inventory/master/types	
/api/inventory/master/locations	
All with: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE



